runs.text:
Official Music Video for "I Thank God" featuring JWLKRS Worship, Blake Wiggins & Ryan Ellis.

“I Thank God” was written by Jesse Cline, Maryanne J George, Dante Bowe, Aaron Moses, Chuck Butler, & Enrique Holmes. This single is from Housefires’ new upcoming album, “How To Start A Housefire Part 2” releasing April 21. 

PRE-ORDER "How to Start a Housefire Part 2"

Stream I Thank God from “How To Start A Housefire Part 2” Available Now!
Link:

YouTube @jwlkrsworship 

LYRICS
Verse 1
Wandering into the night
Wanting a place to hide
This weary soul
This bag of bones
And I try with all my might
But I just can't win the fight
I'm slowly drifting
A vagabond

Pre-Chorus 1 
And just when
I ran out of road
I met a Man I didn't know
And He told me
That I was not alone

Chorus
He picked me up
He turned me around
He placed my feet on solid ground
I thank the Master
I thank the Savior
Because He healed my heart
He changed my name
Forever free, I'm not the same
I thank the Master
I thank the Savior
I thank God

Verse 2
I cannot deny what I see
Got no choice but to beliеve
My doubts are burning
Like ashеs in the wind
So, so long to my old friends
Burden and bitterness
You can just keep it moving, hey
Nah, you ain't welcome here

Pre-Chorus 2
From now 'til
I walk the streets of gold
I'll sing of how
You saved my soul
This wayward son has found
His way back home

Bridge
Oh, hell lost another one
I am free
I am free
I am free

Vamp
Get up, get up, get up
Get up outta that grave

channelTaglineRenderer.content: What began as an experiment and our team asking the question, what if we focused on curating, capturing and releasing the most powerful worship moments we experience to the world? Over 250 million streams, 1M Youtube subscribers and countless stories of people encountering God through worship, we realized we were on to something.

channelMetadataRenderer.title: TRIBL
channelMetadataRenderer.description:
What began as an experiment and our team asking the question, what if we focused on curating, capturing and releasing the most powerful worship moments we experience to the world? Over 250 million streams, 1M Youtube subscribers and countless stories of people encountering God through worship, we realized we were on to something. 

Maverick City Music was the genesis and Tribl is the evolution. 

#unitingthetribes
